  <text>
      <body>
         <div type="entry">
            <pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary25.jpg"/>
            <dateline><date when="1862-01-18">Saturday, January 18.</date></dateline>
            <p><persName><persName key="Charles Kleckner" ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper087">Charles Kleckner</persName></persName>, a Lieut in the 48th, was on board yesterday. One of the
               funniest things that has occurred is <persName subtype="Dick" cert="high" key="Dick Coulter" ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper025" type="real">Dick's</persName> last merchantile transaction. He
               bought a box of <objectName>cigars</objectName>, 100, of the sutler for five dollars, and went upstairs
               and commenced selling them out at 3 cents apiece. The sutler went up after
               while and told him he was losing 2 cents on every <objectName>cigar</objectName>. He was astounded and sold at 6, then became disgusted and sold at five. He managed to get out with
               losing 25 cents, according to his own account. He paid that much for his
               experience and will probably not embark on any more. We parted our cable <time>this morning</time> in trying to get clear of a bark, and got aground, and spent most of
               <time>the morning</time> trying to get loose. We are still aground. <persName subtype="Reno" key="Gen. Jesse Reno" ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper086">Reno</persName> said we must be
               over the swash t<time>omorrow morning</time>, and <time>this evening</time>, we are [onclad?] to get out, arms and acoustic [events?] on board some tugs who are to take us over. Another <objectName type="vehicle">gunboat</objectName> was sunk today, so we have lost two <objectName type="vehicle">gunboats</objectName>, a <objectName type="vehicle">schooner</objectName> or two - several <objectName type="vehicle">ships</objectName> are fast aground. <persName role="Reporter" subtype="Carpenter" key="Mr. Carpenter" ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper092">Mr Carpenter</persName> reports for [?], was on board <time>this morning</time>.
               Also <persName role="Captain" subtype="Potts" key="Capt. Potts" ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper093">Capt. Potts</persName> of <placeName role="City" subtype="Reading" key="Reading" ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl074">Reading</placeName> or <placeName role="City" subtype="Pottsville" key="Pottsville" ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl099">Pottsville</placeName>. The day has been <name type="weather">cold and windy</name>. The
               <name type="weather">sun</name> came out <time>this evening</time>, but this is a dreary day [wast?]. I could not sleep <time>last night</time>, and<time> this afternoon</time>, my bones ache all over. I hope I am not going to be
               sick, and that it is only temporary, from being confined on board so closely, and
               from want of exercise. see [ante?] for conclusion.</p>
         </div>
